Q2No one knew about genes, DNA or chromosomes
when Mendel was still alive, so the significance of his
work wasn’t realised until after he had died.
These days people recognise Mendel as one of the founding
fathers of genetics. He was just a bit ahead of his time.
The yellow hereditary unit is dominant, so if the pea plant
has both yellow and green hereditary units its seeds will
be yellow. If the plant just has yellow hereditary units its
seeds will also be yellow. For its seeds to be green, the
plant has to have two of the green hereditary units.

Sex-linked disorders are usually due to a faulty allele
on the X chromosome. Women need two copies
of the recessive allele to have an X-linked recessive
disorder, while men only need one copy.
